<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Voices from
the Verge</b></p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Side 2B</b></p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Introduction</b></p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Operator 21O </b>
<p class="para">There is a delay
in our scheduled correspondence from the Council of Humanity. All
communication personnel should carry out designated confirmation
protocols.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Operator 6O </b>
<p class="para">Hmm... I feel
like there's a lot of noise mixed in with this data. I wonder what it
is? ... Wait. This isn't noise.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Operator 21O </b>
<p class="para">Commencing scan.
If you don't get anything after four seconds, try a pattern
comparison.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Operator 6O </b>
<p class="para">Hold on. This was
in a message from the council...</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Operator 21O </b>
<p class="para">The Commander...
Contact the Commander! Hurry!</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Operator 6O </b>
<p class="para">I can't! All the
ports have been destroyed, and...</p>
<p class="para">​</p>
<p class="para">(The stage
flashes red. The word Error appears on the screen while a siren goes
off.) (Maniacal laughter)</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Operator 21O </b>
<p class="para">The infection
is...</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Operator 6O </b>
<p class="para">No... Noooooo!</p>
<p class="para"><br/>
<br/>

</p>
<p class="para">--</p>
<p class="para">— <b>Crumbling
Lies</b> —</p>
<p class="para">June 26, 11945</p>
<p class="para">1:12 AM: Logic
virus outbreak occurs within the Bunker satellite base.<br/>
1:23 AM:
Virus spreads to the Information Control Team.<br/>
1:25 AM: All
external communication channels are cut off.<br/>
1:47 AM: Firefights
between maintenance workers break out in the hangar.<br/>
1:49 AM:
Nearly all YoRHa members are infected.<br/>
2:05 AM: Infected YoRHa
members wreak havoc in the command room.<br/>
2:18 AM: Fires break
out in multiple living quarters.<br/>
2:20 AM: An explosion occurs
near the Bunker's fusion reactor.<br/>
2:28 AM: YoRHa units 2B and 9S
escape the Bunker.<br/>
2:30 AM: The Bunker falls. YoRHa is
annihilated.</p>
<p class="para">--</p>
<p class="para">— <b>A
Beautiful Song</b> —</p>
<p class="para">The Bunker that
was our home fell. The council of Humanity we believed in was a lie.
Herein lies a record that has never been disclosed: A record of
sights witnessed by 2B and 9S within a memory. Sights seen as they
travelled a world mired in absurdity and deceit.</p>
<p class="para">--</p>
<p class="para">​</p>
<p class="para">(2B Ragged
breathing)</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Guess...this is
it...</p>
<p class="para">​</p>
<p class="para">(Thrusting her
sword into a stone)</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">These are...my
memories. Take care of everyone for me... Take care...of the
future... A2...</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Act 1: A City
Without Memories</b></p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">What is this
place? Pod, perform a scan of the periphery. Pod, come in! Where are
you!?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">The spacious
expanse where 2B find herself is eerily quiet. Her voice scatters and
disappears into the ether as she speaks. She is surrounded by a vast
city robbed of color. White buildings are covered by an all-devouring
canopy of pure white that blankets the sky.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">YoRHa unit 2B
located.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Pod 153! Where's
9S!?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">Unknown. We were
separated while withdrawing from the front line.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Check for black
box signals.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">Negative. No such
check is possible due to communications in the area being jammed.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Then use your
sensors to perform a scan of the periphery.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">Analysis: No
lifeform signatures detected nearby. However, the precision of this
information is 39.1% lower than normal as it is not possible to
connect to the network.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">It is a puzzling
situation in a puzzling space. 2B places her hand on her chest.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">This isn't right.
I should be dead.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">She recalls the
feeling of cold steel being plunged into her chest. She recalls the
stillness in A2's eyes. The event is stored clear as day in her
memory banks.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">There's also no
sign of the virus that infected my body. Pod. What is the likelihood
we're in cyberspace?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">Hypothesis: There
is a 0.2987% chance of this being a cyberspace. Based on matter
present in the atmosphere and materials used in nearby buildings,
there is a 99.7013% chance of this space existing in the material
world. Alert: There is a widely held belief that pinching one's cheek
is an effective course of action in such situations. Do you require
your cheek pinched?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">That won't be
necessary.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">2B finds herself
at a loss. Is there truly still hope? Or is there simply more despair
to come?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">9S...</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">No Prayer will be
answered. The future remains closed. But simply waiting around is not
an option.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">We're getting out
of here— and we're going to save 9S.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">Affirmative. This
Pod will commence support of YoRHa unit 2B.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">A black shadow
dashes through the white expanse. She must put an end to this cycle
of tragedy, even if it is all without meaning.</p>
<p class="para">--</p>
<p class="para">(A2 Groaning)</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">Despite being
caught in the collapse of the city ruins, A2 made it through intact.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">Nnngh...
god...damnnit! Move, you piece of junk!</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">She awakens to a
body in great pain from head to toe. A body that will not do as she
commands. Spewing abuses in disdain of this development, A2 managed
to rise to her feet.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">Where the hell am
I?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">Cold white
buildings are lined throughout the space. Hollow light pours down
from an impossibly clear sky. As A2 takes a step, something emerges
from a nearby box.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">...A hologram?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">The
three-dimensional image of a robot wearing a hat bows in A2's
direction. Then, As if on cue, machines in the area awaken one after
the other. Their speakers blare the same phrase repeatedly, as if
attempting to brainwash the listener. A light attached to a building
projects an image on the ground. It is what was referred to in the
old world as an “advertisement.”</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">Buzz off, you
freakin' scrapheaps!</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">Without a second
thought, A2 launches an offensive, scattering fragments of destroyed
machines across the ground.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">That should shut
things up around here... Huh?</p>
<p class="para">​</p>
<p class="para">(Emil Cheerful
Humming)</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">A2 hears an
easygoing song that fits poorly with her surroundings, as well as the
piercing sound of an engine. Though far away, it gradually draws
closer.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">Seriously?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">Oh no, somebody's
in the way! Better pump the breaks and stop on the double!</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">As A2 worries the
shrill sound of braking may have shattered her eardrums, the odor of
burnt rubber assaults her nasal passages.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">What a stench!</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">S-sorry...</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">A bizarre face is
attached to the body of an aged car. Though its appearance is
suspicious, A2 doesn't seem wary in the slightest.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">Emil. What are
you doing here?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">So the city
suddenly collapsed, right? And then these big white buildings shot
straight up from the ground like BOOM! I tried to escape by jumping
across collapsing footholds, but I didn't have the horsepower.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">I see.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">It was pretty
crazy! ...Hey, where are you going?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">I'm gonna blow
this joint. Being surrounded by noisy-ass machines isn't my thing.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">Then let me tag
along! I can't get any business done down here anyways. You don't
mind, right?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">Makes no
difference to me. If you can't keep up, I'll just leave you behind
anyways.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">They are amidst a
sea of perfectly white buildings. In both shape and form, it is an
exact replica of a human city from the old world. Skyscrapers that
stand among the clouds. Highways which stretch in all directions.
Deluges of light and information. An uninhabited city filled with
objects symbolizing humanity's prosperity.<font face="Arial, sans-serif"> </font>
<font face="Arial, sans-serif"> </font> And now, A2 and Emil wander
this unfamiliar place in search of a way out.</p>
<p class="para"><br/>
<br/>

</p>
<p class="para">--</p>
<p class="para">— <b>Peaceful
Sleep </b>—</p>
<p class="para">--</p>
<p class="para">— <b>City Ruins</b>
—</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2003 / 12 </b>
<p class="para">A strange disease
of unknown origin emerges, one which causes people to turn white and
transform into salt. It begins to spread like wildfire.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2025 / 01 </b>
<p class="para">A technology is
discovered that enables the separation and preservation of a human's
body and soul.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2061 / 12 </b>
<p class="para">The process of
separating humans is completed. It is decided that humanity will wait
until a treatment for the disease has been found.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">5012 / 08 </b>
<p class="para">Aliens from outer
space invade and launch an attack across the entire planet.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">11732 / 03 </b>
<p class="para">A large-scale
counteroffensive staged by the androids managing Earth ends in
failure.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">11940 / 12 </b>
<p class="para">To bring an end
to the deadlocked war, the newest models of androids are assembled to
form an organization called “YoRHa.”</p>
<p class="para"><br/>
<br/>

</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Act 2: An
Encounter Forgotten</b></p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">No matter how far
we go, all the buildings look same.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">I'm sick of
walking around like a chump. You've got gunpowder, right? Let's blast
our way through.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">How about we take
a look in that direction this time? We might find something.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">Did you not hear
me? Where's the gunpowder at? Let's get explode-y.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">What fantastic
weather! Not a cloud in the sky.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">Quit acting like
you don't hear me, you rusty jalopy.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">Footsteps and the
sound of an engine echo throughout the colorless, empty city. But
while the strange sights may be eerie, the city doesn't once bare its
fangs at the pair. Yet A2 still moves to grasp her weapon. She points
the blade at the space between two buildings, towards an alley
shrouded in shadow.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">All right. The
hell are you following us around for?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">...A2?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">A girl clad in
white emerges from the alley. Her hands tremble slightly, perhaps in
fear of the weapon pointed at her.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">??? </b>
<p class="para">I'm sorry. It's
just... I've never seen people here before.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">A2, Wait! Please
put your weapon away!</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">A2 raises a
slight eyebrow at Emil's plea. She's never seen him show so much
emotion before.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">You know this
kid?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Emil </b>
<p class="para">I'm not sure. I
lost a bunch of memories while multiplying myself, so there's a lot I
don't really remember very well. But if there's one thing I do know,
it's this: We absolutely must not hurt her!</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">It would be a
tall order for A2 to be convinced by Emil's entirely unreasonable
explanation. But while his face looks like little more than a strange
mask with a moving mouth, A2 somehow sees Emil's yearning for days
long past within his gaze. She puts away her weapon and turns to the
girl.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">You got a name?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">After a moment's
hesitation, the girl's small lips begin to move.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">??? </b>
<p class="para">Yonah.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">A2 </b>
<p class="para">What are you
doing here?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Yonah </b>
<p class="para">We live in this
city. Me and my brother.</p>
<p class="para"><br/>
<br/>

</p>
<p class="para">--</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">Though the space
extends without end, the methodically designed city holds no warmth.
And the sheer white buildings that scrape at the heavens look almost
like pillars of salt.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">Yonah! Where are
you. Yonah!?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">A young man pants
as he runs in search of his little sister—his only family. There is
nothing he wouldn't sacrifice to protect her.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">Yonah!</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">Pain shoots
through his throat as he screams. He has not has a single drop of
water since the previous day. Ignoring his parched throat, he comes
to a stop. He sees a dark shadow move in the corner of his vision.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">...!</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">The shadow beings
to a woman in a black blindfold. To her side, a small iron box floats
in midair.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Pod. Scan for
machine lifeforms.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">Sufficient data
cannot be acquired due to jammed communications.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">What are people
doing here? Are you the ones who took Yonah!?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">As the young man
tightens his grip on the iron pipe in his hand, the woman assumes a
combat stance in response.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">Proposal: Do not
engage. Due to the number of uncertainties in play, gathering
additional information is the most effective course of action.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">And eliminating
him would give us one less uncertainty to worry about.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">What!?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">We are isolated
within a city of unknown location. Act of provocation are not
recommended. Proposal: Pursue cooperative relationships with
lifeforms capable of communication, rather than engaging in
hostilities.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">I've got no
obligation to help out complete strangers.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">Negative. The
matter at hand is not an obligation. Wanton combat reduces the
likelihood of returning alive. There are 38 additional demerits.
Which I shall now enumerate. Number one—</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Quiet, you.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">What the hell's
going on here?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 042
(Narration) </b>
<p class="para">Perhaps
succumbing to Pod's persuasion, The two combatants slowly lower their
arms.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">You alone?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">I've got a
sister. We live together. How about you?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Just me and that
pod there. We're looking for a way out of this city. You know
anything about that?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">Nope. This city's
so big, I haven't been able to see all of it. Never reached any kind
of dead end, either.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Fine. Tell me how
you got here.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">I don't know. My
sister and I just sort of showed up one day.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">How long have you
been here?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">Couldn't say. The
sun doesn't set here, so part of me thinks it's just been a few days,
but... There's another part that feels like I've been here for
months. Say, did you happen to see a little girl on your way here?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">No. You're the
first person we've met.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">How about boxes
filled with food or water?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Nothing like that
either. Do such goods even exist in this city?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">You see them
every now and then. They're how we've been able to survive. But
lately you have to go pretty far afield if you want to find any.
Yonah—that's my sister— probably went out to look for food. I'd
been away from our house for a lot longer than usual, so...</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">.....</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">Proposal: Assist
with the search.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">Huh!? You'll help
me?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">2B </b>
<p class="para">Why, Pod?</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Pod 153 </b>
<p class="para">We currently
possess no information regarding a way out. Refusing to assist will
have no impact on our likelihood of discovering an exit. However,
people who have been here longer than us likely possess more
information than we do. There is a high probability that assisting in
the search will yield information regarding a means of escape.</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Nier </b>
<p class="para">If you help me
look for Yonah, I'll tell you everything I know.</p>
